---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

const article = { author: "Maine Dispensary Guide Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-15", modifiedDate: "2026-03-28", section: "City Guides" };
---

<Layout 
  title="Bangor Dispensary Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to opening a cannabis dispensary in Bangor, Maine. Detailed analysis of Northern Maine market opportunities, local regulations, and licensing requirements."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507090960745-b32f65d3113a?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
  article={article}
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Bangor Dispensary Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How to open a cannabis dispensary in Bangor, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <section class="fact-box">
      <h2>📋 Bangor at a Glance</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>License Required</strong></td><td>Maine OCP Adult-Use Retail License</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Local Fee</strong></td><td>$2,500 annually (varies by zone)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>School Buffer</strong></td><td>500 ft minimum</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Operating Hours</strong></td><td>8 AM - 10 PM (state-mandated)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Commercial Rent</strong></td><td>$10-18/sq ft annually</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Current Dispensaries</strong></td><td>4-5 (underserved market)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why Bangor?</h2>
      <p>Bangor is Maine's third-largest city and the commercial heartbeat of northern New England. With a metropolitan population exceeding 100,000 and remarkably low competition, Bangor offers everything you're looking for: room to grow, a loyal customer base, and first-mover advantage.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="A Hub of Opportunity" type="passion">
      Bangor isn't just a city; it's the gateway to Northern Maine. The community here values local business and authenticity. If you build a brand that respects the local character while providing professional service, you'll find a fiercely loyal following that the more saturated southern markets can't match.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Bangor Market Data</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Metro Population</td><td>100,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Primary Industries</td><td>Healthcare, Education, Retail, Military</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Current Competition</td><td>Low — significant opportunity</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Median Household Income</td><td>$52,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Access</td><td>I-95, Route 1A, Bangor International Airport</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local X-Factor: The Northern Maine Gateway</h2>
      <p><strong>What sets Bangor apart:</strong> Bangor draws customers from throughout northern and central Maine—a catchment area of 100,000+ residents who currently have limited dispensary options. Many travel 60+ miles to Portland for quality products.</p>
      <p><strong>Strategic Implication:</strong> First-movers in Bangor can capture regional loyalty. Customers will travel to Bangor from as far as Aroostook County, creating a customer base that extends far beyond city limits.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Regulations</h2>
      <p>Bangor permits cannabis retail under state regulations:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>State license required</strong> — OCP Adult-Use Retail</li>
        <li><strong>Local zoning</strong> — Must be in permitted commercial zone</li>
        <li><strong>Local fee</strong> — Approximately $2,500 annually</li>
        <li><strong>Distance requirements</strong> — 500 ft from schools, 300 ft from churches</li>
        <li><strong>Security requirements</strong> — Standard OCP requirements apply</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Best Locations in Bangor</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Area</th><th>Pros</th><th>Cons</th><th>Rent/Sq Ft</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Hammond Street</strong></td><td>Downtown, good traffic</td><td>Limited parking</td><td>$15-18</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Union Street</strong></td><td>Highway visibility, retail corridor</td><td>Less character</td><td>$12-16</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Stillwater Avenue</strong></td><td>Shopping area, easy access</td><td>Competition nearby</td><td>$14-17</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Bangor Mall Area</strong></td><td>Regional traffic, national anchor tenants</td><td>Suburban feel</td><td>$10-14</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>✅ Opportunity:</strong> Underserved market with 100K+ regional population</li>
        <li><strong>✅ Advantage:</strong> First-mover opportunity still available</li>
        <li><strong>💰 Investment:</strong> Lower costs than Portland—$250K-350K startup</li>
        <li><strong>📍 Location:</strong> Hammond Street for downtown; Union Street for visibility</li>
        <li><strong>🔗 Strategy:</strong> Build regional brand to capture northern Maine customers</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Apply for <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/adult-use/applications-forms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">state license</a> through OCP</li>
        <li>Identify location in permitted commercial zone</li>
        <li>Verify distance requirements with city planning</li>
        <li>Review <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-security/">security requirements</a></li>
        <li>Prepare <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-business-plan/">business plan</a></li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.bangormaine.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">City of Bangor</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">Maine Dispensary License Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-real-estate/">Real Estate & Zoning Guide</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This information is for informational purposes only. Verify current requirements with OCP and the City of Bangor before applying.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.1); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary); }
  .fact-box h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box table { margin: 0; }
</style>